3Cp%3EThen%2C%20we%20categorized%20our%20priorities%20into%20three%20areas%3A%20things%20that%20need%20professional%20subcontractor%20work%2C%20small%20expenses%2C%20and%20those%20that%20only%20require%20elbow%20grease.%20We%20spread%20the%20expense%20of%20subcontractors%20by%20working%20on%20the%20elbow-grease%20projects%20in%20between%2C%20such%20as%20steam-mopping%20the%20bathrooms%2C%20resealing%20grout%2C%20and%20cleaning%20trim%20and%20baseboards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20we%20saved%20up%20credit-card%20points%20and%20took%20advantage%20of%20sales%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Famazon-prime-day%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20Prime%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20smaller%20upgrades%20like%20hardware%2C%20light-switch%20panels%2C%20cable%20hiders%2C%20and%20storage%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpacing%20things%20out%20and%20doing%20them%20one%20at%20a%20time%20helps%20spread%20out%20and%20delay%20the%20cost%20and%20gives%20me%20more%20time%20to%20research%20exactly%20what%20I%20want%20for%20every%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EInvestment%20accounts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20math%20teacher%20once%20told%20me%20I%20would%20only%20make%20a%20finite%20amount%20of%20money%20in%20my%20lifetime%20and%20then%20showed%20a%20graph%20explaining%20the%20growth%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexponential-growth-moores-law-compound-interest-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexponential%20interest%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHewing%20to%20that%20basic%20concept%20helped%20me%20prioritize%20saving%20in%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eretirement%20accounts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20my%2020s%2C%20even%20when%20it%20was%20a%20stretch%20or%20strain%20on%20the%20budget.%20Often%2C%20when%20I%20job-hopped%2C%20my%20401(k)%20got%20kicked%20out%20from%20the%20employer%20after%20a%20while%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20I%20only%20freelanced%2C%20I%20didn't%20have%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20these%20times%2C%20I%20put%20my%20retirement%20savings%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20my%20credit%20union%2C%20so%20the%20administration%20part%20was%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20hit%20my%2030s%2C%20that%20account%20had%20enough%20money%20to%20buy%20into%20a%20clean-energy%20IRA%20fund%20with%20a%20%245%2C000%20minimum%20investment.%20I%20still%20have%20a%20rolling%20401(k)%20with%20my%20current%20full-time%20employer%2C%20who%20makes%20a%2010%25%20match%20to%20my%20contributions%2C%20and%20my%20spouse%20has%20an%20employer%20401(k)%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fretirement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehealth%20savings%20account%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiscretionary%20spending%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20a%20spreadsheet%20in%20my%2020s%20helped%20me%20determine%20and%20balance%20my%20top%20discretionary%20expenditures%3A%20groceries%2C%20hygiene%20and%20beauty%2C%20clothing%2C%20and%20going%20out%20and%20entertainment.%20I%20always%20ensure%20these%20categories%20are%20paid%20in%20cash%20and%20pay%20my%20credit-card%20bill%20in%20full%20monthly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPracticing%20this%20in%20my%2020s%20helps%20me%20now%20as%20grocery%20expenses%20rise%20and%20my%20student-loan%20payment%20of%20around%20%24150%20a%20month%20has%20come%20back%20into%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20that%20%26quot%3BHomebucks%26quot%3B%20(what%20I%20call%20not%20going%20to%20Starbucks%20and%20eating%20out%20less)%20doesn't%20save%20me%20much%20money%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmeal-prepping-how-to-stay-on-track-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emeal-prepping%3C%2Fa%3E%20saves%20me%20time%2C%20so%20I%20do%20it.%20I%20freeze%20egg%20muffins%20and%20cook%20a%20batch%20of%20chili%20chicken%20for%20tostadas%2C%20burritos%2C%20or%20taco%20night.%20We%20have%20an%20espresso%20machine%20and%20a%20French%20press%2C%20which%20helps%20us%20avoid%20buying%20coffee%20out%20and%20makes%20adding%20a%20coffee%20creamer%20to%20the%20grocery%20list%20a%20nice%20treat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20some%20expenses%20increase%20uncontrollably%2C%20I%20look%20for%20discretionary%20expenses%20I%20can%20comfortably%20cut%2C%20like%20winterizing%20certain%20beauty%20habits%20or%20going%20longer%20between%20appointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20my%20nails%20done%20is%20tempting%2C%20so%20I%20splurged%20on%20a%20UV%2FLED%20light%20to%20upgrade%20my%20game%20and%20do%20them%20myself.%20Brand-name%20clothing%20is%20also%20very%20tempting%2C%20but%20my%20rule%20is%20to%20save%20up%20my%20monthly%20clothing%20budget%20until%20I%20have%20the%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20monthly%20beauty-box%20subscription%20in%20my%2020s%2C%20which%20is%20a%20great%20way%20to%20try%20new%20things%20and%20stock%20up.%20Now%20in%20my%2030s%2C%20my%20hair-care%2C%20skincare%2C%20and%20makeup%20stash%20is%20much%20larger%2C%20so%20I%20use%20the%20%26quot%3Breplacement%20only%2C%20don't%20buy%26quot%3B%20method%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FMakeupRehab%2Fwiki%2Ffaq%2Fphrase-guide%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Er%2Fmakeuprehab%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%2020s%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20to%20try%20every%20happy%20hour%20and%20rooftop%20bar%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20get%20out%20of%20my%20small%20apartment.%20Now%2C%20I've%20been%20there%2C%20and%20I%20enjoy%20staying%20home.%20A%20bag%20of%20frozen%20fries%20curbs%20the%20happy-hour%20cravings%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHobbies%3C%2Fs